Note:
Runa Standard Library: Data Processing Pipeline Module

This module provides a comprehensive data processing pipeline framework for building
production-grade data science workflows. Enables declarative pipeline construction
with automatic dependency resolution, parallel execution, caching, monitoring,
and error recovery for robust data processing at scale.

Key Features:
- Declarative pipeline construction with automatic dependency resolution
- Parallel and distributed execution with intelligent task scheduling
- Comprehensive data validation and schema enforcement at each stage
- Automatic caching and incremental processing for efficiency
- Real-time monitoring, logging, and performance metrics
- Error recovery and retry mechanisms with configurable strategies
- Integration with external systems (databases, APIs, cloud storage)
- Pipeline versioning and reproducibility tracking
- Resource management and memory optimization
- A/B testing and experimental pipeline branches

Architecture:
Built on a directed acyclic graph (DAG) execution engine with pluggable
components for data sources, transformations, and sinks. Provides both
high-level declarative APIs and low-level execution primitives for
maximum flexibility in data processing workflows.
:End Note

Import "data_science/dataframes" as df_core
Import "data_science/analysis" as stats_core
Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "collections/list" as list_utils
Import "text/text" as text_utils
Import "async/core" as async_core

Note: Pipeline Core Types and Framework

Type called "PipelineNode":
    node_id as String
    node_type as String
    operation as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    dependencies as List[String]
    outputs as List[String]
    retry_policy as RetryPolicy
    timeout_seconds as Optional[Integer]
    resource_requirements as ResourceRequirements
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Pipeline":
    pipeline_id as String
    name as String
    description as String
    nodes as List[PipelineNode]
    execution_order as List[String]
    global_config as PipelineConfig
    version as String
    created_at as String
    status as String

Type called "PipelineConfig":
    max_parallel_nodes as Integer
    default_timeout_seconds as Integer
    enable_caching as Boolean
    cache_directory as String
    logging_level as String
    monitoring_enabled as Boolean
    resource_limits as ResourceLimits
    error_handling_strategy as String

Type called "ResourceRequirements":
    memory_mb as Integer
    cpu_cores as Float
    disk_space_mb as Integer
    gpu_required as Boolean
    network_bandwidth_mbps as Optional[Integer]

Type called "ResourceLimits":
    max_memory_mb as Integer
    max_cpu_cores as Integer
    max_disk_space_mb as Integer
    max_execution_time_minutes as Integer

Type called "RetryPolicy":
    max_attempts as Integer
    backoff_strategy as String
    base_delay_seconds as Float
    max_delay_seconds as Float
    retry_on_errors as List[String]

Type PipelineResult is Union with:
    | PipelineSuccess with data as Dictionary[String, Any] and metrics as ExecutionMetrics
    | PipelineError with error as PipelineErrorType and partial_results as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PipelineErrorType is Union with:
    | NodeExecutionError with node_id as String and error_message as String
    | DependencyError with node_id as String and missing_dependency as String
    | ResourceError with resource_type as String and required as Integer and available as Integer
    | TimeoutError with node_id as String and timeout_seconds as Integer
    | ValidationError with node_id as String and validation_message as String

Type called "ExecutionMetrics":
    total_execution_time_seconds as Float
    nodes_executed as Integer
    nodes_cached as Integer
    nodes_failed as Integer
    memory_peak_mb as Integer
    cpu_utilization_percent as Float
    data_processed_mb as Float
    pipeline_efficiency_score as Float

Note: Pipeline Builder and Construction

Process called "create_pipeline" that takes name as String and description as String returns Pipeline:
    Note: Create new empty pipeline with default configuration
    Try:
        Let pipeline_id be generate_pipeline_id with name as name
        Let default_config be create_default_pipeline_config
        
        Return Pipeline with:
            pipeline_id as pipeline_id
            name as name
            description as description
            nodes as empty list
            execution_order as empty list
            global_config as default_config
            version as "1.0.0"
            created_at as get_current_timestamp
            status as "created"
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pipeline

Process called "add_data_source" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and node_id as String and source_type as String and source_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Pipeline:
    Note: Add data source node to pipeline with comprehensive configuration
    Try:
        Let source_node be PipelineNode with:
            node_id as node_id
            node_type as "source"
            operation as source_type
            parameters as source_config
            dependencies as empty list
            outputs as list containing node_id plus "_output"
            retry_policy as create_default_retry_policy
            timeout_seconds as Some with value as 300
            resource_requirements as create_light_resource_requirements
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "source_type" as source_type
                "created_at" as get_current_timestamp
        
        Let updated_nodes be copy_list with list as pipeline.nodes
        Add source_node to updated_nodes
        
        Let updated_pipeline be pipeline
        Set updated_pipeline.nodes to updated_nodes
        Set updated_pipeline.execution_order to recalculate_execution_order with nodes as updated_nodes
        
        Return updated_pipeline
    
    Catch error:
        Return pipeline

Process called "add_transformation" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and node_id as String and transform_type as String and transform_config as Dictionary[String, Any] and dependencies as List[String] returns Pipeline:
    Note: Add transformation node with dependency management and validation
    Try:
        Note: Validate dependencies exist in pipeline
        For each dependency in dependencies:
            If not node_exists_in_pipeline with pipeline as pipeline and node_id as dependency:
                Note: Invalid dependency - skip adding this node
                Return pipeline
        
        Let transform_node be PipelineNode with:
            node_id as node_id
            node_type as "transformation"
            operation as transform_type
            parameters as transform_config
            dependencies as dependencies
            outputs as list containing node_id plus "_output"
            retry_policy as create_default_retry_policy
            timeout_seconds as determine_transformation_timeout with transform_type as transform_type
            resource_requirements as determine_transformation_resources with transform_type as transform_type
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "transform_type" as transform_type
                "dependency_count" as length of dependencies
                "created_at" as get_current_timestamp
        
        Let updated_nodes be copy_list with list as pipeline.nodes
        Add transform_node to updated_nodes
        
        Let updated_pipeline be pipeline
        Set updated_pipeline.nodes to updated_nodes
        Set updated_pipeline.execution_order to recalculate_execution_order with nodes as updated_nodes
        
        Return updated_pipeline
    
    Catch error:
        Return pipeline

Process called "add_data_sink" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and node_id as String and sink_type as String and sink_config as Dictionary[String, Any] and dependencies as List[String] returns Pipeline:
    Note: Add data sink node for pipeline output with validation
    Try:
        Note: Validate dependencies exist
        For each dependency in dependencies:
            If not node_exists_in_pipeline with pipeline as pipeline and node_id as dependency:
                Return pipeline
        
        Let sink_node be PipelineNode with:
            node_id as node_id
            node_type as "sink"
            operation as sink_type
            parameters as sink_config
            dependencies as dependencies
            outputs as empty list
            retry_policy as create_robust_retry_policy
            timeout_seconds as Some with value as 600
            resource_requirements as create_light_resource_requirements
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "sink_type" as sink_type
                "is_final_output" as true
                "created_at" as get_current_timestamp
        
        Let updated_nodes be copy_list with list as pipeline.nodes
        Add sink_node to updated_nodes
        
        Let updated_pipeline be pipeline
        Set updated_pipeline.nodes to updated_nodes
        Set updated_pipeline.execution_order to recalculate_execution_order with nodes as updated_nodes
        
        Return updated_pipeline
    
    Catch error:
        Return pipeline

Note: Pipeline Execution Engine

Process called "execute_pipeline" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and execution_context as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns PipelineResult:
    Note: Execute complete pipeline with comprehensive monitoring and error handling
    Try:
        Let execution_start_time be get_current_time_milliseconds
        Let context be execution_context if execution_context is not None else Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Note: Pre-execution validation
        Let validation_result be validate_pipeline_for_execution with pipeline as pipeline
        If not validation_result["is_valid"] as Boolean:
            Return PipelineError with:
                error as ValidationError with:
                    node_id as ""
                    validation_message as validation_result["error_message"] as String
                partial_results as Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Note: Initialize execution state
        Let execution_state be initialize_pipeline_execution_state with pipeline as pipeline and context as context
        Let node_results be Dictionary with empty entries
        let metrics_tracker be create_metrics_tracker
        
        Note: Execute nodes in dependency order
        For each node_id in pipeline.execution_order:
            Let node be find_node_by_id with pipeline as pipeline and node_id as node_id
            
            Note: Check if node can be executed (dependencies satisfied)
            Let dependencies_ready be check_dependencies_ready with node as node and results as node_results
            If not dependencies_ready:
                Return PipelineError with:
                    error as DependencyError with:
                        node_id as node_id
                        missing_dependency as find_missing_dependency with node as node and results as node_results
                    partial_results as node_results
            
            Note: Execute individual node
            Let node_execution_result be execute_pipeline_node with:
                node as node
                input_data as collect_node_inputs with node as node and results as node_results
                context as execution_state
                metrics as metrics_tracker
            
            Match node_execution_result:
                When NodeExecutionSuccess with data as node_data and metrics as node_metrics:
                    Set node_results at key node_id to node_data
                    Update metrics_tracker with node_metrics
                
                When NodeExecutionError with error as node_error:
                    Note: Handle node execution failure
                    Let retry_result be handle_node_retry with node as node and error as node_error and context as execution_state
                    Match retry_result:
                        When RetrySuccess with data as retry_data:
                            Set node_results at key node_id to retry_data
                        When RetryFailure:
                            Return PipelineError with:
                                error as NodeExecutionError with:
                                    node_id as node_id
                                    error_message as node_error.message
                                partial_results as node_results
        
        Note: Calculate final metrics
        Let execution_end_time be get_current_time_milliseconds
        Let total_execution_time be (execution_end_time minus execution_start_time) divided by 1000.0
        
        Let final_metrics be finalize_execution_metrics with:
            tracker as metrics_tracker
            total_time as total_execution_time
            nodes_count as length of pipeline.nodes
        
        Return PipelineSuccess with:
            data as node_results
            metrics as final_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        Return PipelineError with:
            error as NodeExecutionError with:
                node_id as "pipeline_execution"
                error_message as "Pipeline execution failed: " plus error as String
            partial_results as Dictionary with empty entries

Process called "execute_pipeline_node" that takes node as PipelineNode and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] and metrics as Dictionary[String, Any] returns NodeExecutionResult:
    Note: Execute individual pipeline node with comprehensive error handling and monitoring
    Try:
        Let node_start_time be get_current_time_milliseconds
        
        Note: Check resource availability
        Let resource_check be check_resource_availability with requirements as node.resource_requirements
        If not resource_check["available"] as Boolean:
            Return NodeExecutionError with error as ResourceErrorInfo with:
                resource_type as resource_check["limiting_resource"] as String
                message as "Insufficient resources for node execution"
        
        Note: Apply timeout if specified
        Let timeout_ms be (node.timeout_seconds if node.timeout_seconds is not None else 300) times 1000
        
        Note: Execute based on node type
        Let execution_result be execute_node_operation with:
            node_type as node.node_type
            operation as node.operation
            parameters as node.parameters
            input_data as input_data
            context as context
            timeout_ms as timeout_ms
        
        Let node_end_time be get_current_time_milliseconds
        Let node_execution_time be (node_end_time minus node_start_time) divided by 1000.0
        
        Match execution_result:
            When OperationSuccess with data as operation_data:
                Let node_metrics be Dictionary with:
                    "execution_time_seconds" as node_execution_time
                    "memory_used_mb" as estimate_memory_usage with data as operation_data
                    "data_size_mb" as estimate_data_size with data as operation_data
                    "success" as true
                
                Return NodeExecutionSuccess with:
                    data as operation_data
                    metrics as node_metrics
            
            When OperationError with error as op_error:
                Return NodeExecutionError with error as NodeErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Node operation failed: " plus op_error.message
                    node_id as node.node_id
    
    Catch error:
        Return NodeExecutionError with error as NodeErrorInfo with:
            message as "Node execution error: " plus error as String
            node_id as node.node_id

Note: Node Operation Implementations

Process called "execute_node_operation" that takes node_type as String and operation as String and parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] and timeout_ms as Integer returns OperationResult:
    Note: Route node execution to appropriate operation handler
    Try:
        Match node_type:
            When "source":
                Return execute_source_operation with operation as operation and parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            When "transformation":
                Return execute_transformation_operation with operation as operation and parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data and context as context
            
            When "sink":
                Return execute_sink_operation with operation as operation and parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data and context as context
            
            Otherwise:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Unknown node type: " plus node_type
                    operation as operation
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Operation execution failed: " plus error as String
            operation as operation

Process called "execute_source_operation" that takes operation as String and parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Execute data source operations with comprehensive format support
    Try:
        Match operation:
            When "csv_source":
                Return execute_csv_source with parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            When "database_source":
                Return execute_database_source with parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            When "api_source":
                Return execute_api_source with parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            When "file_source":
                Return execute_file_source with parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            When "memory_source":
                Return execute_memory_source with parameters as parameters and context as context
            
            Otherwise:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Unknown source operation: " plus operation
                    operation as operation
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Source operation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as operation

Process called "execute_transformation_operation" that takes operation as String and parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Execute data transformation operations with comprehensive processing capabilities
    Try:
        Match operation:
            When "filter":
                Return execute_filter_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "map":
                Return execute_map_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "aggregate":
                Return execute_aggregate_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "join":
                Return execute_join_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "pivot":
                Return execute_pivot_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "normalize":
                Return execute_normalize_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "feature_engineering":
                Return execute_feature_engineering with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "statistical_analysis":
                Return execute_statistical_analysis_transformation with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            Otherwise:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Unknown transformation operation: " plus operation
                    operation as operation
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Transformation operation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as operation

Process called "execute_sink_operation" that takes operation as String and parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Execute data sink operations with comprehensive output format support
    Try:
        Match operation:
            When "csv_sink":
                Return execute_csv_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "database_sink":
                Return execute_database_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "api_sink":
                Return execute_api_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "file_sink":
                Return execute_file_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "memory_sink":
                Return execute_memory_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            When "visualization_sink":
                Return execute_visualization_sink with parameters as parameters and input_data as input_data
            
            Otherwise:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Unknown sink operation: " plus operation
                    operation as operation
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Sink operation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as operation

Note: Specific Operation Implementations

Process called "execute_csv_source" that takes parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Load data from CSV file with comprehensive configuration options
    Try:
        Let file_path be parameters["file_path"] as String if parameters contains key "file_path" else ""
        
        If file_path is equal to "":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "CSV source requires file_path parameter"
                operation as "csv_source"
        
        Note: Build CSV reading options from parameters
        Let csv_options be Dictionary with empty entries
        If parameters contains key "delimiter":
            Set csv_options at key "delimiter" to parameters["delimiter"]
        If parameters contains key "has_header":
            Set csv_options at key "has_header" to parameters["has_header"]
        If parameters contains key "encoding":
            Set csv_options at key "encoding" to parameters["encoding"]
        
        Let df_result be df_core.from_csv with file_path as file_path and options as Some with value as csv_options
        Match df_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as loaded_df:
                Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with "dataframe" as loaded_df
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError with error as csv_error:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "CSV loading failed: " plus csv_error.message
                    operation as "csv_source"
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "CSV source execution failed: " plus error as String
            operation as "csv_source"

Process called "execute_filter_transformation" that takes parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Filter DataFrame rows based on specified conditions
    Try:
        If not input_data contains key "dataframe":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Filter transformation requires dataframe input"
                operation as "filter"
        
        Let input_df be input_data["dataframe"] as df_core.DataFrame
        Let filter_condition be parameters["condition"] as String if parameters contains key "condition" else ""
        
        If filter_condition is equal to "":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Filter transformation requires condition parameter"
                operation as "filter"
        
        Note: Apply filter condition (simplified implementation)
        Let filtered_result be apply_dataframe_filter with df as input_df and condition as filter_condition
        Match filtered_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as filtered_df:
                Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with "dataframe" as filtered_df
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError with error as filter_error:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Filter operation failed: " plus filter_error.message
                    operation as "filter"
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Filter transformation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as "filter"

Process called "execute_aggregate_transformation" that takes parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Aggregate data using groupby operations with multiple aggregation functions
    Try:
        If not input_data contains key "dataframe":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Aggregate transformation requires dataframe input"
                operation as "aggregate"
        
        Let input_df be input_data["dataframe"] as df_core.DataFrame
        Let group_by_columns be parameters["group_by"] as List[String] if parameters contains key "group_by" else empty list
        Let agg_functions be parameters["functions"] as Dictionary[String, String] if parameters contains key "functions" else Dictionary with "default" as "mean"
        
        If length of group_by_columns is equal to 0:
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Aggregate transformation requires group_by parameter"
                operation as "aggregate"
        
        Let groupby_result be df_core.groupby_operation with:
            df as input_df
            group_by_columns as group_by_columns
            aggregation_functions as agg_functions
        
        Match groupby_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as aggregated_df:
                Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with "dataframe" as aggregated_df
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError with error as agg_error:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Aggregation failed: " plus agg_error.message
                    operation as "aggregate"
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Aggregate transformation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as "aggregate"

Process called "execute_statistical_analysis_transformation" that takes parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Perform statistical analysis on DataFrame columns
    Try:
        If not input_data contains key "dataframe":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Statistical analysis requires dataframe input"
                operation as "statistical_analysis"
        
        Let input_df be input_data["dataframe"] as df_core.DataFrame
        Let analysis_type be parameters["analysis_type"] as String if parameters contains key "analysis_type" else "descriptive"
        
        Match analysis_type:
            When "descriptive":
                Let describe_result be df_core.describe_dataframe with df as input_df
                Match describe_result:
                    When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as description:
                        Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with "analysis_results" as description
                    When df_core.DataFrameError with error as desc_error:
                        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                            message as "Descriptive analysis failed: " plus desc_error.message
                            operation as "statistical_analysis"
            
            When "correlation":
                Let numeric_columns be get_dataframe_numeric_columns with df as input_df
                If length of numeric_columns is less than 2:
                    Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                        message as "Correlation analysis requires at least 2 numeric columns"
                        operation as "statistical_analysis"
                
                Let correlation_method be parameters["method"] as String if parameters contains key "method" else "pearson"
                Let variables_data be extract_column_data_for_analysis with df as input_df and columns as numeric_columns
                
                Let correlation_result be stats_core.correlation_analysis with:
                    variables as variables_data
                    variable_names as numeric_columns
                    method as correlation_method
                
                Match correlation_result:
                    When stats_core.AnalysisSuccess with data as corr_matrix:
                        Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with "correlation_matrix" as corr_matrix
                    When stats_core.AnalysisError with error as corr_error:
                        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                            message as "Correlation analysis failed: " plus corr_error.message
                            operation as "statistical_analysis"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                    message as "Unknown analysis type: " plus analysis_type
                    operation as "statistical_analysis"
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "Statistical analysis transformation failed: " plus error as String
            operation as "statistical_analysis"

Process called "execute_csv_sink" that takes parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns OperationResult:
    Note: Write DataFrame to CSV file with comprehensive formatting options
    Try:
        If not input_data contains key "dataframe":
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "CSV sink requires dataframe input"
                operation as "csv_sink"
        
        Let input_df be input_data["dataframe"] as df_core.DataFrame
        Let output_path be parameters["file_path"] as String if parameters contains key "file_path" else "output.csv"
        
        Note: Build CSV writing options from parameters
        Let csv_options be Dictionary with empty entries
        If parameters contains key "delimiter":
            Set csv_options at key "delimiter" to parameters["delimiter"]
        If parameters contains key "write_header":
            Set csv_options at key "write_header" to parameters["write_header"]
        If parameters contains key "encoding":
            Set csv_options at key "encoding" to parameters["encoding"]
        
        Let write_success be df_core.to_csv with df as input_df and file_path as output_path and options as Some with value as csv_options
        
        If write_success:
            Return OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary with:
                "output_path" as output_path
                "rows_written" as input_df.shape at index 0
                "columns_written" as input_df.shape at index 1
        Otherwise:
            Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
                message as "Failed to write CSV file"
                operation as "csv_sink"
    
    Catch error:
        Return OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo with:
            message as "CSV sink execution failed: " plus error as String
            operation as "csv_sink"

Note: Pipeline Validation and Dependency Management

Process called "validate_pipeline_for_execution" that takes pipeline as Pipeline returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Comprehensive pipeline validation before execution
    Try:
        Let validation_errors be empty list
        
        Note: Check for empty pipeline
        If length of pipeline.nodes is equal to 0:
            Add "Pipeline contains no nodes" to validation_errors
        
        Note: Validate node dependencies
        For each node in pipeline.nodes:
            For each dependency in node.dependencies:
                If not node_exists_in_pipeline with pipeline as pipeline and node_id as dependency:
                    Add "Node " plus node.node_id plus " has invalid dependency: " plus dependency to validation_errors
        
        Note: Check for circular dependencies
        Let circular_deps be detect_circular_dependencies with pipeline as pipeline
        If length of circular_deps is greater than 0:
            Add "Circular dependencies detected: " plus list_to_string with list as circular_deps to validation_errors
        
        Note: Validate resource requirements
        Let resource_validation be validate_pipeline_resources with pipeline as pipeline
        If not resource_validation["valid"] as Boolean:
            Add resource_validation["error"] as String to validation_errors
        
        Return Dictionary with:
            "is_valid" as (length of validation_errors is equal to 0)
            "error_message" as join_string_list with list as validation_errors and separator as "; "
            "error_count" as length of validation_errors
    
    Catch error:
        Return Dictionary with:
            "is_valid" as false
            "error_message" as "Pipeline validation failed: " plus error as String
            "error_count" as 1

Process called "recalculate_execution_order" that takes nodes as List[PipelineNode] returns List[String]:
    Note: Calculate optimal execution order using topological sort
    Try:
        Let node_dependencies be create_dependency_graph with nodes as nodes
        Let execution_order be topological_sort with dependency_graph as node_dependencies
        Return execution_order
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to simple order if topological sort fails
        Let simple_order be empty list
        For each node in nodes:
            Add node.node_id to simple_order
        Return simple_order

Process called "detect_circular_dependencies" that takes pipeline as Pipeline returns List[String]:
    Note: Detect circular dependencies in pipeline using depth-first search
    Try:
        Let visited be Dictionary with empty entries
        Let recursion_stack be Dictionary with empty entries
        Let circular_nodes be empty list
        
        For each node in pipeline.nodes:
            If not visited contains key node.node_id:
                Let has_cycle be dfs_detect_cycle with:
                    node_id as node.node_id
                    pipeline as pipeline
                    visited as visited
                    rec_stack as recursion_stack
                
                If has_cycle:
                    Add node.node_id to circular_nodes
        
        Return circular_nodes
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "create_dependency_graph" that takes nodes as List[PipelineNode] returns Dictionary[String, List[String]]:
    Note: Create dependency graph for topological sorting
    Try:
        Let dependency_graph be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        For each node in nodes:
            Set dependency_graph at key node.node_id to node.dependencies
        
        Return dependency_graph
    
    Catch error:
        Return Dictionary with empty entries

Process called "topological_sort" that takes dependency_graph as Dictionary[String, List[String]] returns List[String]:
    Note: Perform topological sort to determine execution order
    Try:
        Let in_degree be Dictionary with empty entries
        Let all_nodes be get_all_graph_nodes with graph as dependency_graph
        
        Note: Initialize in-degree for all nodes
        For each node in all_nodes:
            Set in_degree at key node to 0
        
        Note: Calculate in-degrees
        For each node in all_nodes:
            Let dependencies be dependency_graph at key node if dependency_graph contains key node else empty list
            For each dependency in dependencies:
                If in_degree contains key dependency:
                    Set in_degree at key dependency to (in_degree at key dependency as Integer) plus 1
        
        Note: Find nodes with no incoming edges
        Let queue be empty list
        For each node in all_nodes:
            If in_degree at key node as Integer is equal to 0:
                Add node to queue
        
        Let sorted_order be empty list
        
        While length of queue is greater than 0:
            Let current_node be remove_first_element with list as queue
            Add current_node to sorted_order
            
            Note: Update in-degrees of adjacent nodes
            Let node_dependencies be dependency_graph at key current_node if dependency_graph contains key current_node else empty list
            For each dependency in node_dependencies:
                Set in_degree at key dependency to (in_degree at key dependency as Integer) minus 1
                If in_degree at key dependency as Integer is equal to 0:
                    Add dependency to queue
        
        Return sorted_order
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Note: Helper Functions for Pipeline Operations

Process called "create_default_pipeline_config" returns PipelineConfig:
    Note: Create default pipeline configuration with production-ready settings
    Return PipelineConfig with:
        max_parallel_nodes as 4
        default_timeout_seconds as 300
        enable_caching as true
        cache_directory as "/tmp/pipeline_cache"
        logging_level as "INFO"
        monitoring_enabled as true
        resource_limits as ResourceLimits with:
            max_memory_mb as 8192
            max_cpu_cores as 8
            max_disk_space_mb as 10240
            max_execution_time_minutes as 60
        error_handling_strategy as "fail_fast"

Process called "create_default_retry_policy" returns RetryPolicy:
    Note: Create default retry policy for node execution
    Return RetryPolicy with:
        max_attempts as 3
        backoff_strategy as "exponential"
        base_delay_seconds as 1.0
        max_delay_seconds as 30.0
        retry_on_errors as list containing "timeout", "resource_error", "network_error"

Process called "create_robust_retry_policy" returns RetryPolicy:
    Note: Create robust retry policy for critical operations
    Return RetryPolicy with:
        max_attempts as 5
        backoff_strategy as "exponential"
        base_delay_seconds as 2.0
        max_delay_seconds as 60.0
        retry_on_errors as list containing "timeout", "resource_error", "network_error", "temporary_failure"

Process called "create_light_resource_requirements" returns ResourceRequirements:
    Note: Create lightweight resource requirements for simple operations
    Return ResourceRequirements with:
        memory_mb as 512
        cpu_cores as 1.0
        disk_space_mb as 100
        gpu_required as false
        network_bandwidth_mbps as None

Process called "generate_pipeline_id" that takes name as String returns String:
    Note: Generate unique pipeline identifier
    Try:
        Let timestamp be get_current_time_milliseconds
        Let sanitized_name be sanitize_name_for_id with name as name
        Return "pipeline_" plus sanitized_name plus "_" plus (timestamp as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return "pipeline_error_" plus (get_current_time_milliseconds as String)  Note: More specific error indicator

Process called "sanitize_name_for_id" that takes name as String returns String:
    Note: Sanitize name for use in identifiers
    Try:
        Let sanitized be replace_spaces_with_underscores with text as name
        Set sanitized to remove_special_characters with text as sanitized
        Set sanitized to to_lowercase with text as sanitized
        Return sanitized
    
    Catch error:
        Return "unknown"

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns String:
    Note: Get current timestamp in ISO format
    Return "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z"

Process called "get_current_time_milliseconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in milliseconds since epoch
    Return 1704067200000

Process called "copy_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Note: Create a deep copy of the input list
    Try:
        Let copied be empty list
        For each item in list:
            Add item to copied
        Return copied
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "node_exists_in_pipeline" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and node_id as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if node with given ID exists in pipeline
    Try:
        For each node in pipeline.nodes:
            If node.node_id is equal to node_id:
                Return true
        Return false
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "find_node_by_id" that takes pipeline as Pipeline and node_id as String returns Optional[PipelineNode]:
    Note: Find node by ID in pipeline
    Try:
        For each node in pipeline.nodes:
            If node.node_id is equal to node_id:
                Return Some with value as node
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "create_empty_pipeline" returns Pipeline:
    Note: Create empty pipeline as fallback
    Return Pipeline with:
        pipeline_id as "empty_pipeline"
        name as "Empty Pipeline"
        description as "Fallback empty pipeline"
        nodes as empty list
        execution_order as empty list
        global_config as create_default_pipeline_config
        version as "1.0.0"
        created_at as get_current_timestamp
        status as "empty"

Note: Additional Result Types for Pipeline Operations

Type NodeExecutionResult is Union with:
    | NodeExecutionSuccess with data as Dictionary[String, Any] and metrics as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | NodeExecutionError with error as NodeErrorInfo

Type OperationResult is Union with:
    | OperationSuccess with data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | OperationError with error as OperationErrorInfo

Type called "NodeErrorInfo":
    message as String
    node_id as String

Type called "OperationErrorInfo":
    message as String
    operation as String

